Spine cord descompresion and instrumentation in a case of solid aneurysmal bone cyst in the lumbar spine. We report a 8-year-old boy with two month history of pain and stiffness in his left lower extremity. On x-ray, MRI and scintigraphy examinations a lytic lesion affecting the body and posterior arc of his third lumbar vertebral become evident. The tumour was excised through a double, anterior and posterior approach spinal fusion with posterior transpedicular instrumentation was also performed in the same procedure